reply_text:
@miolol3120 Man y’all overdoing this wailing

I loved the ending regardless f the popular opinion, the conclusion the author chose for this was something bittersweet it was executed so beautifully that it harvested the right emotions in yall, i get it all that resentment y’all have against the conclusion comes from anguish and misery caused by the perpetrators that never matched with their justice those VIPs and morbid frontman deserved the worst but by the end of S2 it was obvious they were so established and branched they couldn’t have won against them. 

In my perspective Gi Hun’s arc start to finish in retrospect was so beautiful
